summary: Absent Minded
title: Absent Minded
body:
Who wants to bet that Caduceus is not actually the best team player, not because he doesn’t want to be but because he seldom had to think about other people’s opinions, safety, or wants very often so he’s not always great remembering that stuff or communicating what’s going on in his head.

Like he’s super considerate when he remembers, but he might not think there’s something wrong with just wandering off to do his own thing and then forgetting to tell the rest of the team. 

Tangent: Do you think it’s hard to lose a 7-foot pink firbolg in a crowd because they got distracted by something? Also, do you think Fjord has a new found anxiety about this teammates being out of sight for too long?

summary: I really like how travis and marisha really embody their characters. Like they all do, but these two its the most noticable i...
body:
I really like how travis and marisha really embody their characters. Like they all do, but these two its the most noticable i guess. 

Body launguage wise even if you watched marisha ray play beau and keyleth while it was muted you can tell that there is two entirely different energies there. Keyleth was all about grand gestures, big sweeping hand movements, big grins. None of it particularly elegant and even when she did something super cool she would off set it with a goofy look and a classic keyleth line. Beau on the other hand sits oddly in chairs, her movements are small but powerful, everything has a purpose. She hardly moves her hands when shes talking for example. 

Fjord and grog are very similar. Travis really puffed out his chest and sat up straight and tall. Even just watching grog felt big and powerful and sure of himself and almost never paying attention if there was too much talking. With Fjord he keeps his shoulders low and tucked, the way someone whos been made fun of their whole life for their look would be, only straightening to cast a spell or swing his fachion aka when fjord feels powerful. Not even mentioning the looks on his face when hes listening and watching.
